description.p:
A solution of the invention is a process for producing hydrogen and capturing carbon dioxide in a hydrogen generation plant, the process comprising the steps of:
a) subjecting a synthesis gas 15 coming from a synthesis gas producing unit 31 to a process unit 0 to obtain a hydrogen product stream 23 and a hydrogen depleted process stream 1;
b) compressing , cooling to a temperature equal to or less than -10°C , and purifying/separating - each operation in one or more steps and in any order - at least a portion of the process stream 1 in a carbon dioxide separation unit 4 to produce a carbon dioxide rich liquid stream 6 and a carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream 5;
c) withdrawing the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream 5 from the carbon dioxide separation unit 4 and passing the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream 5 through a hydrogen selective membrane separation unit 7 to form a hydrogen rich permeate stream 8 with the remaining components in the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream 5 forming a hydrogen lean residue stream 9;
d) passing the hydrogen lean residue stream 9 through a carbon dioxide selective membrane separation unit 10 to form a carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream 11 with the remaining components in the hydrogen lean residue stream 9 forming a carbon dioxide depleted residue stream 12;
e) optionally compressing the hydrogen rich permeate stream 8 or a part of it, in a compressor 13 and recycling at least a part of the hydrogen rich permeate stream 8 for use as a supplemental feed stream in the synthesis gas producing unit 31, the process unit 0 or in both, and/or as a fuel for the synthesis gas producing unit;
f) recycling at least a part of the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream 11 to the carbon dioxide separation unit 4 in the process stream 1 prior to the compression or within the compression between stages of compression, or compressing the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream 11 in another compressor and recycling the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream 11 in the carbon dioxide separation unit 4 and recycling the carbon dioxide depleted residue stream 12 to be used as a supplemental feed stream for the synthesis gas producing unit 31 and/or as a fuel for the synthesis gas producing unit 31 or for steam regeneration or in another process.

According to particular embodiments of the present invention, the process is characterized by the following characteristics:
a hydrocarbon containing feed stream 16 is treated in a synthesis gas producing unit 31 to obtain a synthesis gas 15.
a portion at least of the carbon dioxide depleted residue stream 12 is used as a fuel.
at least a portion of the hydrogen product stream 23 is used as a fuel for the synthesis gas producing unit 31 or as fuel for steam generation;
the overall capture rate of carbon dioxide from the hydrogen production process is equal to or greater than 80%;
the process unit 0 is a pressure swing adsorption unit and the process stream 1 is a tail gas from the pressure swing adsorption unit;
the synthesis gas producing unit 31 is a hydrocarbon Steam Reformer;
the separation and purification of the cooled process stream in the carbon dioxide separation unit 8 is carried out by single or multi-step partial liquefaction, compression and distillation or any combination of single or multi-step partial liquefaction, compression and distillation;
the carbon dioxide rich liquid stream 9 that is withdrawn is vaporized to produce a carbon dioxide rich gas stream or pumped and optionally heated to produce a high pressure CO2 stream;
the process stream 1 is subjected to a purification unit to remove impurities such as water, hydrocarbons, alcohols, NH3, H2S.., and preferentially the purification unit comprises an adsorption unit;
the process stream 1 is compressed to a pressure above 35 bar abs and is cooled to a temperature equal to or less than -30°C;
the hydrogen rich permeate stream 8 is subjected to a shift reaction in an optional water gas shift reactor 32 prior to being recycled to the water gas shift reactor 21, the process unit 0 or both the water gas shift unit 21 and the process unit 0, pref. the water gas shift reactor 32 is a low temperature water gas shift reactor;
the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream 5 is subjected to a shift reaction in an optional water gas shift reactor 33 prior to being passed thorough the hydrogen and carbon dioxide membrane separation units (7, 10).pref the water gas shift reactor 33 is a low temperature water gas shift reactor;
the hydrogen rich permeate stream 5 is split into a primary fraction of the first hydrogen rich permeate stream 5.1 to be used as a supplemental feed stream to be added to the synthesis gas stream 24 prior to being introduced into the water gas shift reactor 25 and a secondary fraction of the first hydrogen rich permeate stream 5.2 to be used as a supplemental feed stream to be added to the feed gas 19 prior to being introduced into the pressure swing adsorption unit 0 with the proportion of each fraction depending upon the percentage of production in the steam methane reformer 19;
the hydrogen rich permeate stream 5 or the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream 11 or both of them are withdrawn as 2 -or more- permeate streams at different pressures.

claim.claim-text:
A process for producing hydrogen and capturing carbon dioxide in a hydrogen generation plant, the process comprising the steps of:
a) subjecting a synthesis gas (15) coming from a synthesis gas producing unit (31) to a process unit (0) to obtain a hydrogen product stream (23) and a hydrogen depleted process stream (1);
b) compressing, cooling to a temperature equal to or less than -10°C, and purifying/separating at least a portion of the process stream (1) in a carbon dioxide separation unit (4) to produce a carbon dioxide rich liquid stream (6) and a carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream (5);
c) withdrawing the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream (5) from the carbon dioxide separation unit (4) and passing the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream (5) through a hydrogen selective membrane separation unit (7) to form a hydrogen rich permeate stream (8) with the remaining components in the carbon dioxide lean non-condensable stream (5) forming a hydrogen lean residue stream (9);
d) passing the hydrogen lean residue stream (9) through a carbon dioxide selective membrane separation unit (10) to form a carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream (11) with the remaining components in the hydrogen lean residue stream (9) forming a carbon dioxide depleted residue stream (12);
e) optionally compressing the hydrogen rich permeate stream (8) or a part of it, in a compressor (13) and recycling at least a part of the hydrogen rich permeate stream (8) for use as a supplemental feed stream in the synthesis gas producing unit (31), the process unit (0) or in both, and/or as a fuel for the synthesis gas producing unit ;
f) recycling at least a part of the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream (11) to the carbon dioxide separation unit (4) in the process stream (1) prior to the compression or within the compression between stages of compression, or compressing the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream (11) in another compressor and recycling the carbon dioxide enriched permeate stream (11) in the carbon dioxide separation unit (4) and recycling the carbon dioxide depleted residue stream (12) to be used as a supplemental feed stream for the synthesis gas producing unit (31) and/or as a fuel for the synthesis gas producing unit (31) or for steam regeneration or in another process.
